column71: 002/003 mix 3% freshly made in the morning of the trial
column124: Portable dope tank and pump - Coag bath BL 0.88m, 60 deg 70% DMSO, 002/003 3% spin finish used in main spin finish bath with a roller pressure of 1.8 Bar and 10:1 (water:002) was used in the lick roller to minimise potential glueing during carbonisation as the 003 component has been identified as contributing to the glueing in carbonisation. The lick roller was set at 13 rpm. Warmup SP8 sample collected for 10 minutes. Running well ie no flaring and no neps, but there were some fibres sticky to the final wash roller. The fibre was opaque indicating that it will have a low density and has been overstretched in either the washing step, hot water stretch or steam stretch. Wash pressure was set to 10.
